5','Healthcare','Cardio-metabolic diseases','Cardiovascular','Heart failure',48,'Heart failure, also known as congestive heart failure, is a syndrome, a group of signs and symptoms, caused by an impairment of the hearts blood pumping function. Symptoms typically include shortness of breath, excessive fatigue, and leg swelling. The shortness of breath may occur with exertion or while lying down, and may wake people up during the night. Chest pain, including angina, is not usually caused by heart failure, but may occur if the heart failure was caused by a heart attack. The severity of the heart failure is mainly decided based on ejection fraction and also measured by the severity of symptoms. Other conditions that may have symptoms similar to heart failure include obesity, kidney failure, liver disease, anemia, and thyroid disease. Common causes of heart failure include coronary artery disease, heart attack, high blood pressure, atrial fibrillation, valvular heart disease, excessive alcohol consumption, infection, and cardiomyopathy.','{\"pat_doc\": 5696.0, \"pub_alt\": 20133.0, \"pub_doc\": 88927.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 4089.0, \"clinic_alt\": 886.0, \"clinic_doc\": 5877.0, \"grant_fund\": 2086191711.0, \"pat_granted\": 1561.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 60.6, \"pub_doc\": 1207.9, \"clinic_doc\": 749.7, \"grant_fund\": -131899850.5, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('ba8da26721789f129302df15eeaef542','525ddc02deb579259414604666af7d2e','e910bc33478f3cb83e3ef258c7d92a6c','2023-09-08 02:02:55','2023-10-28 14:55:06','Healthcare','Fertility','Novel therapies','Gonadotropin-Releasing-Hormone Agonist',12,'A gonadotropin-releasing hormone agonist is a type of medication which affects gonadotropins and sex hormones. They are used for a variety of indications including in fertility medicine and to lower sex hormone levels in the treatment of hormone-sensitive cancers such as prostate cancer and breast cancer, certain gynecological disorders like heavy periods and endometriosis, high testosterone levels in women, early puberty in children, as a part of transgender hormone therapy, and to delay puberty in transgender youth among other uses. It is also used in the suppression of spontaneous ovulation as part of controlled ovarian hyperstimulation, an essential component in in IVF. GnRH agonists are given by injections into fat, as implants placed into fat, and as nasal sprays.','{\"pat_doc\": 0.0, \"pub_alt\": 0.0, \"pub_doc\": 0.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 0.0, \"clinic_alt\": 0.0, \"clinic_doc\": 0.0, \"grant_fund\": 0.0, \"pat_granted\": 0.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 0.0, \"pub_doc\": 0.1, \"clinic_doc\": 0.0, \"grant_fund\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('baa959527f48b24c0877a32af754ea34','b5180881c0acd170e35e7e2628346b44','6f23015b34810fffb37ea505c3bdbd67','2023-09-05 19:31:51','2023-10-29 05:01:13','Life Science','Next Generation Biology','Tissue and Cell Culture','Cell Culture',12,'Cell culture or tissue culture is the process by which cells are grown under controlled conditions, generally outside of their natural environment. The term \"tissue culture\" was coined by American pathologist Montrose Thomas Burrows. This technique is also called micropropagation. After the cells of interest have been isolated from living tissue, they can subsequently be maintained under carefully controlled conditions. They need to be kept at body temperature in an incubator. These conditions vary for each cell type, but generally consist of a suitable vessel with a substrate or rich medium that supplies the essential nutrients, growth factors, hormones, and gases, and regulates the physio-chemical environment. Most cells require a surface or an artificial substrate to form an adherent culture as a monolayer, whereas others can be grown free floating in a medium as a suspension culture.','{\"pat_doc\": 5899.0, \"pub_alt\": 2588.0, \"pub_doc\": 6997.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 559.0, \"clinic_alt\": 504.0, \"clinic_doc\": 179.0, \"grant_fund\": 193482874.0, \"pat_granted\": 2300.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 342.7, \"pub_doc\": -154.3, \"clinic_doc\": 41.7, \"grant_fund\": -133904294.6, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('bacf0537af4514a93e79bf7b4e14e01c','8c13cdcd2f46fbd04ad49b8164252967','b347f7200b8aff24464a347c263147e9','2023-09-08 09:25:33','2023-10-28 21:06:12','Life Science','Sustainability/Core','Separations','Filtration',36,'Filtration is a physical separation process that separates solid matter and fluid from a mixture using a filter medium that has a complex structure through which only the fluid can pass. Solid particles that cannot pass through the filter medium are described as oversize and the fluid that passes through is called the filtrate. Oversize particles may form a filter cake on top of the filter and may also block the filter lattice, preventing the fluid phase from crossing the filter, known as blinding. The size of the largest particles that can successfully pass through a filter is called the effective pore size of that filter. The separation of solid and fluid is imperfect; solids will be contaminated with some fluid and filtrate will contain fine particles. Filtration occurs both in nature and in engineered systems; there are biological, geological, and industrial forms.','{\"pat_doc\": 189683.0, \"pub_alt\": 26339.0, \"pub_doc\": 122847.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 3526.0, \"clinic_alt\": 592.0, \"clinic_doc\": 3105.0, \"grant_fund\": 1198544209.0, \"pat_granted\": 133933.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 616.9, \"pub_doc\": 2964.5, \"clinic_doc\": 373.4, \"grant_fund\": -100190796.6, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('bb19b4c67599b1746f767edac0b52d89','7cdbaeda7c2e92f0a0d7bcfe3cd23472','e2d4dfcdd74fd300c5581dfc34bfe679','2023-09-05 22:19:06','2023-10-28 12:10:33','Electronics','Devices','Next Generation Computers','Brain-computer interfaces',12,'A brainâ€“computer interface, sometimes called a brainâ€“machine interface or smartbrain, is a direct communication pathway between the brains electrical activity and an external device, most commonly a computer or robotic limb. BCIs are often directed at researching, mapping, assisting, augmenting, or repairing human cognitive or sensory-motor functions. They are often conceptualized as a humanâ€“machine interface that skips the intermediary component of the physical movement of body parts, although they also raise the possibility of the erasure of the discreteness of brain and machine. Implementations of BCIs range from non-invasive and partially invasive to invasive, based on how close electrodes get to brain tissue.','{\"pat_doc\": 75.0, \"pub_alt\": 954.0, \"pub_doc\": 650.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 26.0, \"clinic_alt\": 0.0, \"clinic_doc\": 7.0, \"grant_fund\": 12915993.0, \"pat_granted\": 20.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 20.1, \"pub_doc\": 77.8, \"clinic_doc\": 0.6, \"grant_fund\": -3687771.2, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('bba6545b61f6496253ec6e929f508725','233fd598fd0386ae12fee35e82334037','bd1c38b04e309caf5a996a81284254cb','2023-09-04 19:01:17','2023-10-29 06:26:11','Life Science','Sustainability/Core','New Materials','Nanomaterial',36,'Nanomaterials describe, in principle, materials of which a single unit is sized between 1 and 100 nm. Nanomaterials research takes a materials science-based approach to nanotechnology, leveraging advances in materials metrology and synthesis which have been developed in support of microfabrication research. Materials with structure at the nanoscale often have unique optical, electronic, thermo-physical or mechanical properties. Nanomaterials are slowly becoming commercialized and beginning to emerge as commodities.','{\"pat_doc\": 4588.0, \"pub_alt\": 1172.0, \"pub_doc\": 51348.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 2459.0, \"clinic_alt\": 1.0, \"clinic_doc\": 13.0, \"grant_fund\": 1010881672.0, \"pat_granted\": 1388.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 290.2, \"pub_doc\": 1878.6, \"clinic_doc\": 1.8, \"grant_fund\": -70327657.9, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('bc4712a5306b29a9fcc427415a592b4b','c3be1591926e87743c4c54d7028677c0','ef63c5da9830a0ea9737ee257244ed3a','2023-09-08 00:09:38','2023-10-28 16:36:12','Healthcare','Future therapeutic modalities','Delivery methods','Lentivirus',24,'Lentivirus is a genus of retroviruses that cause chronic and deadly diseases characterized by long incubation periods, in humans and other mammalian species. The genus includes the human immunodeficiency virus, which causes AIDS. Lentiviruses are distributed worldwide, and are known to be hosted in apes, cows, goats, horses, cats, and sheep as well as several other mammals. Lentiviruses can integrate a significant amount of viral complementary DNA into the DNA of the host cell and can efficiently infect nondividing cells, so they are one of the most efficient methods of gene delivery. They can become endogenous, integrating their genome into the host germline genome, so that the virus is henceforth inherited by the hosts descendants.','{\"pat_doc\": 764.0, \"pub_alt\": 1822.0, \"pub_doc\": 2676.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 68.0, \"clinic_alt\": 169.0, \"clinic_doc\": 43.0, \"grant_fund\": 27725686.0, \"pat_granted\": 214.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 17.0, \"pub_doc\": -93.8, \"clinic_doc\": 8.6, \"grant_fund\": -9867775.9, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('bc65be88d0ef9437ad7753c669d7f77f','30f5159f16b7a113dcbf47772afc4c96','0a44fd511d173aa7606e2fa180b97dbd','2023-09-08 02:14:34','2023-10-28 22:51:11','Life Science','Next Generation Biology','Synthetic Biology','Gene Circuits',12,'A gene circuit is a network of genes that work together to produce a certain outcome, such as the regulation of a specific biological process. These circuits function through gene expression, in which certain genes are turned on or off in response to environmental stimuli or cellular signals. The composition of the gene circuit can vary depending on the desired outcome, with different genes and regulatory elements influencing the behavior of the circuit. Gene circuits are important for understanding the complex processes that occur within cells and organisms, and have potential applications in fields such as synthetic biology and gene therapy.','{\"pat_doc\": 7.0, \"pub_alt\": 686.0, \"pub_doc\": 91.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 13.0, \"clinic_alt\": 0.0, \"clinic_doc\": 0.0, \"grant_fund\": 13255278.0, \"pat_granted\": 1.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 0.1, \"pub_doc\": 6.4, \"clinic_doc\": 0.0, \"grant_fund\": -2080968.6, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('bc912fe2cd776783a2287654ec4e7a0f','b3a328f05ef6249fe823d3c8f5701aaf','301cad2a0f77cdfc28e4f33b693d4618','2023-09-04 16:29:35','2023-10-29 07:16:15','Life Science','Lab & Future of the Factory','Sensors, Detection & Analysis','Magnetic Resonance Imaging',12,'Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) is a medical imaging technique that uses a strong magnetic field and radio waves to generate detailed images of the bodys internal structures. The process involves placing the patient in a machine that uses a powerful magnet to align the hydrogen atoms in their body. A short pulse of radio waves is then used to disrupt this alignment, causing the atoms to release energy that is detected by a scanner. The data collected is processed by a computer to produce detailed images of the target area. MRI is a non-invasive and highly precise diagnostic tool that can provide information about various conditions including tumors, infections, injuries, and abnormalities in organs and tissues. It is used in a wide range of medical applications, including neurology, cardiology, orthopedics, and oncology.','{\"pat_doc\": 2601.0, \"pub_alt\": 4540.0, \"pub_doc\": 26008.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 590.0, \"clinic_alt\": 632.0, \"clinic_doc\": 3589.0, \"grant_fund\": 457184407.0, \"pat_granted\": 971.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": -32.4, \"pub_doc\": 760.2, \"clinic_doc\": 884.6, \"grant_fund\": -78449677.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}');
INSERT INTO `radar_metrics` VALUES ('bcafe91b7bf782fb71189ea204d5da1a','6df6cc21f2a3ec039f6f594cd9050b81','22c986a1ed138cca635623e24850cd2d','2023-09-08 02:47:18','2023-10-28 14:05:05','Healthcare','Fertility','Novel Drug Delivery','Progesterone supplementation',48,'Progesterone supplementation, also known as progesterone therapy, is a medical treatment that involves taking supplemental doses of progesterone hormone. Progesterone is naturally produced by the ovaries during a womans menstrual cycle and plays a crucial role in regulating the menstrual cycle and preparing the body for pregnancy. However, some women may have low levels of progesterone, resulting in irregular menstrual cycles or difficulty getting pregnant. Progesterone supplementation can help balance hormonal levels and increase the chances of conceiving and sustaining a pregnancy. It can be administered through various methods, such as pills, injections, or vaginal suppositories, and is usually prescribed by a healthcare professional based on the patients individual needs and medical history.','{\"pat_doc\": 0.0, \"pub_alt\": 269.0, \"pub_doc\": 172.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 5.0, \"clinic_alt\": 0.0, \"clinic_doc\": 42.0, \"grant_fund\": 733852.0, \"pat_granted\": 0.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 0.0, \"pub_doc\": 2.6, \"clinic_doc\": 3.4, \"grant_fund\": -80930.6, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('bcb9de93673c134e0d6bdbaae0a7b3b6','c42efb8fe2ca41dc7fd5d4dbb0848ed6','7e6689dbdfabd5b7cf95a105e9764132','2023-09-08 09:27:09','2023-10-28 21:01:10','Life Science','Sustainability/Core','Separations','Gas Chromatography',48,'Gas chromatography is a common type of chromatography used in analytical chemistry for separating and analyzing compounds that can be vaporized without decomposition. Typical uses of GC include testing the purity of a particular substance, or separating the different components of a mixture. In preparative chromatography, GC can be used to prepare pure compounds from a mixture. Gas chromatography is also sometimes known as vapor-phase chromatography, or gasâ€“liquid partition chromatography. These alternative names, as well as their respective abbreviations, are frequently used in scientific literature. Gas chromatography is the process of separating compounds in a mixture by injecting a gaseous or liquid sample into a mobile phase, typically called the carrier gas, and passing the gas through a stationary phase. The mobile phase is usually an inert gas or an unreactive gas such as helium, argon, nitrogen or hydrogen.','{\"pat_doc\": 5343.0, \"pub_alt\": 4917.0, \"pub_doc\": 33842.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 618.0, \"clinic_alt\": 100.0, \"clinic_doc\": 119.0, \"grant_fund\": 100022833.0, \"pat_granted\": 2067.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 67.1, \"pub_doc\": 279.0, \"clinic_doc\": 14.9, \"grant_fund\": -2716027.5, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('bcbbf43c5a43a403093058746021a886','ce48dd19951bc72e32788762866aa8ba','9f4de602c8b4dc324f5081159f81d1f9','2023-09-08 10:02:32','2023-10-28 19:21:13','Life Science','Sustainability/Core','Separations','Loss on Drying',12,'Loss on Drying (LOD) is a common analysis performed in the pharmaceutical, food, and cosmetics industries to quantify the amount of moisture content in a sample. It is a gravimetric analysis method that measures the weight lost by a sample when it is heated at a specific temperature. The difference between the initial weight of the sample and the weight after heating is recorded as LOD. This technique is useful in determining the stability and shelf life of products, as high moisture content can lead to microbial growth, chemical degradation, and decreased product quality. LOD is a critical parameter in product manufacturing, as it can affect the products physical and chemical properties, efficacy, and safety. Controlling the moisture content of a product is essential to ensure its stability and prevent spoilage, making LOD an important tool for quality control and assurance.','{\"pat_doc\": 11.0, \"pub_alt\": 8.0, \"pub_doc\": 66.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 0.0, \"clinic_alt\": 0.0, \"clinic_doc\": 0.0, \"grant_fund\": 0.0, \"pat_granted\": 2.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 0.1, \"pub_doc\": 1.4, \"clinic_doc\": -0.8, \"grant_fund\": -10651.8, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('bd302b1686024aab708609e69297f7ca','4ed1727d16902077c7b79a9c262994fa','12a26d07df436f186302cbc8c800d6d6','2023-09-05 20:45:30','2023-10-29 04:31:13','Life Science','Lab & Future of the Factory','Sensors, Detection & Analysis','Electroencephalography',36,'Electroencephalography is a method to record an electrogram of the spontaneous electrical activity of the brain. The biosignals detected by EEG have been shown to represent the postsynaptic potentials of pyramidal neurons in the neocortex and allocortex. It is typically non-invasive, with the EEG electrodes placed along the scalp using the International 10â€“20 system, or variations of it. Electrocorticography, involving surgical placement of electrodes, is sometimes called \"intracranial EEG\". Clinical interpretation of EEG recordings is most often performed by visual inspection of the tracing or quantitative EEG analysis. Voltage fluctuations measured by the EEG bioamplifier and electrodes allow the evaluation of normal brain activity. As the electrical activity monitored by EEG originates in neurons in the underlying brain tissue, the recordings made by the electrodes on the surface of the scalp vary in accordance with their orientation and distance to the source of the activity.','{\"pat_doc\": 483.0, \"pub_alt\": 5051.0, \"pub_doc\": 12600.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 647.0, \"clinic_alt\": 122.0, \"clinic_doc\": 742.0, \"grant_fund\": 224379792.0, \"pat_granted\": 100.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 0.2, \"pub_doc\": 299.2, \"clinic_doc\": 125.2, \"grant_fund\": -19331779.4, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('bd570a8716d25f4fcd383c388e3c0c28','d9d824a70a843cb14f452ee5dfe90190','1c2b4adda3013a6c23af8f23b2fc3d3e','2023-09-08 00:45:08','2023-10-28 11:45:32','Electronics','Devices','Immersive Experience','head-mounted display',48,'A head-mounted display is a display device, worn on the head or as part of a helmet, that has a small display optic in front of one or each eye. An HMD has many uses including gaming, aviation, engineering, and medicine. Virtual reality headsets are HMDs combined with IMUs. There is also an optical head-mounted display, which is a wearable display that can reflect projected images and allows a user to see through it.','{\"pat_doc\": 8326.0, \"pub_alt\": 597.0, \"pub_doc\": 2754.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 134.0, \"clinic_alt\": 2.0, \"clinic_doc\": 83.0, \"grant_fund\": 26152747.0, \"pat_granted\": 3102.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 37.6, \"pub_doc\": 37.6, \"clinic_doc\": 11.9, \"grant_fund\": -2029094.3, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('bd5baadbcfa8fb01c90681521522d39c','b44ddb1f06c55c8a655b7e35627c4216','eb670a907e9a4e83aa692353515a741c','2023-09-05 19:20:24','2023-10-29 05:06:13','Life Science','Sustainability/Core','Formulation','Emulsion',24,'An emulsion is a mixture of two or more liquids that are normally immiscible owing to liquid-liquid phase separation. Emulsions are part of a more general class of two-phase systems of matter called colloids. Although the terms colloid and emulsion are sometimes used interchangeably, emulsion should be used when both phases, dispersed and continuous, are liquids. In an emulsion, one liquid is dispersed in the other. Examples of emulsions include vinaigrettes, homogenized milk, liquid biomolecular condensates, and some cutting fluids for metal working. Two liquids can form different types of emulsions. As an example, oil and water can form, first, an oil-in-water emulsion, in which the oil is the dispersed phase, and water is the continuous phase. Second, they can form a water-in-oil emulsion, in which water is the dispersed phase and oil is the continuous phase. Multiple emulsions are also possible, including a \"water-in-oil-in-water\" emulsion and an \"oil-in-water-in-oil\" emulsion.','{\"pat_doc\": 37615.0, \"pub_alt\": 16313.0, \"pub_doc\": 20280.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 417.0, \"clinic_alt\": 588.0, \"clinic_doc\": 173.0, \"grant_fund\": 108814449.0, \"pat_granted\": 15070.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 8.0, \"pub_doc\": 587.2, \"clinic_doc\": 18.4, \"grant_fund\": -8503567.9, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('bd6a6d148c7e0eca3e45cc04b2d937fe','42a2ae4f376aa262cce85cebcfc87270','feda5fe0c35fb0034afb02626ac53d93','2023-09-08 02:11:05','2023-10-28 23:06:15','Life Science','Next Generation Biology','Cell Detection and Analysis','High-Content Screening',36,'High-content screening, also known as high-content analysis or cellomics, is a method that is used in biological research and drug discovery to identify substances such as small molecules, peptides, or RNAi that alter the phenotype of a cell in a desired manner. Hence high content screening is a type of phenotypic screen conducted in cells involving the analysis of whole cells or components of cells with simultaneous readout of several parameters. HCS is related to high-throughput screening, in which thousands of compounds are tested in parallel for their activity in one or more biological assays, but involves assays of more complex cellular phenotypes as outputs. Phenotypic changes may include increases or decreases in the production of cellular products such as proteins and/or changes in the morphology of the cell. Hence HCA typically involves automated microscopy and image analysis.','{\"pat_doc\": 4.0, \"pub_alt\": 343.0, \"pub_doc\": 285.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 31.0, \"clinic_alt\": 0.0, \"clinic_doc\": 0.0, \"grant_fund\": 14325369.0, \"pat_granted\": 1.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": -0.1, \"pub_doc\": -0.2, \"clinic_doc\": 0.0, \"grant_fund\": -2272629.7, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('bd7d3d0c283f9a2a157548d5150eb39b','40a0355ede62ff4272058fe5b25b12bf','eefb2660a8535eb1d304c9a60295324f','2023-09-05 21:19:43','2023-10-28 17:46:11','Healthcare','Future therapeutic modalities','Delivery methods','Liposomes',24,'A liposome is a small artificial vesicle, spherical in shape, having at least one lipid bilayer. Due to their hydrophobicity and/or hydrophilicity, biocompatibility, particle size and many other properties, liposomes can be used as drug delivery vehicles for administration of pharmaceutical drugs and nutrients, such as lipid nanoparticles in mRNA vaccines, and DNA vaccines. Liposomes can be prepared by disrupting biological membranes. Liposomes are most often composed of phospholipids, especially phosphatidylcholine, and cholesterol, but may also include other lipids, such as those found in egg and phosphatidylethanolamine, as long as they are compatible with lipid bilayer structure. A liposome design may employ surface ligands for attaching to unhealthy tissue. The major types of liposomes are the multilamellar vesicle, the small unilamellar liposome vesicle, the large unilamellar vesicle, and the cochleate vesicle.','{\"pat_doc\": 1557.0, \"pub_alt\": 501.0, \"pub_doc\": 6304.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 217.0, \"clinic_alt\": 108.0, \"clinic_doc\": 46.0, \"grant_fund\": 53400768.0, \"pat_granted\": 412.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 11.3, \"pub_doc\": 166.2, \"clinic_doc\": 8.1, \"grant_fund\": -13776868.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('bd8839159dbea99f49a45fa893036551','00f5350f80c16146d1f1e5be0746e46e','e910bc33478f3cb83e3ef258c7d92a6c','2023-09-08 02:32:48','2023-10-28 14:21:12','Healthcare','Fertility','Novel Drug Delivery','Gonadotropin-Releasing-Hormone Agonist',36,'A gonadotropin-releasing hormone agonist is a type of medication which affects gonadotropins and sex hormones. They are used for a variety of indications including in fertility medicine and to lower sex hormone levels in the treatment of hormone-sensitive cancers such as prostate cancer and breast cancer, certain gynecological disorders like heavy periods and endometriosis, high testosterone levels in women, early puberty in children, as a part of transgender hormone therapy, and to delay puberty in transgender youth among other uses. It is also used in the suppression of spontaneous ovulation as part of controlled ovarian hyperstimulation, an essential component in in IVF. GnRH agonists are given by injections into fat, as implants placed into fat, and as nasal sprays.','{\"pat_doc\": 0.0, \"pub_alt\": 21.0, \"pub_doc\": 1.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 0.0, \"clinic_alt\": 0.0, \"clinic_doc\": 0.0, \"grant_fund\": 0.0, \"pat_granted\": 0.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 0.0, \"pub_doc\": 0.1, \"clinic_doc\": 0.0, \"grant_fund\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('bd884df7c050e2f7b8811348a88ed5dc','73178bcae12bbd288347bb8d8e293d45','9b201e2ee1a601e1d33b326135e74c79','2023-09-08 08:26:31','2023-10-28 10:35:32','Electronics','Devices','Other','4D printing',36,'4-dimensional printing uses the same techniques of 3D printing through computer-programmed deposition of material in successive layers to create a three-dimensional object. However, in 4D printing, the resulting 3D shape is able to morph into different forms in response to environmental stimulus, with the 4th dimension being the time-dependent shape change after the printing. It is therefore a type of programmable matter, wherein after the fabrication process, the printed product reacts with parameters within the environment and changes its form accordingly.','{\"pat_doc\": 357.0, \"pub_alt\": 211.0, \"pub_doc\": 1035.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 45.0, \"clinic_alt\": 0.0, \"clinic_doc\": 0.0, \"grant_fund\": 21359184.0, \"pat_granted\": 133.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 10.9, \"pub_doc\": 86.3, \"clinic_doc\": 0.0, \"grant_fund\": 226691.3, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('bd934e71ddc24af8eb33e8b5d743a765','d26eb2bd1f18468fd4cd16acbcfe71a0','0de5062bb6f653f85fa36c9feb30d5e1','2023-09-08 01:30:22','2023-10-29 00:11:22','Life Science','Lab & Future of the Factory','Automated Systems, Control, & Data','Robotic Process Automation',48,'Robotic process automation is a form of business process automation that is based on software robots or artificial intelligence agents. It is sometimes referred to as software robotics. In traditional workflow automation tools, a software developer produces a list of actions to automate a task and interface to the back end system using internal application programming interfaces or dedicated scripting language. In contrast, RPA systems develop the action list by watching the user perform that task in the applications graphical user interface, and then perform the automation by repeating those tasks directly in the GUI. This can lower the barrier to the use of automation in products that might not otherwise feature APIs for this purpose. RPA tools have strong technical similarities to graphical user interface testing tools. These tools also automate interactions with the GUI, and often do so by repeating a set of demonstration actions performed by a user.','{\"pat_doc\": 1167.0, \"pub_alt\": 119.0, \"pub_doc\": 1111.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 41.0, \"clinic_alt\": 0.0, \"clinic_doc\": 0.0, \"grant_fund\": 7036506.0, \"pat_granted\": 253.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 111.3, \"pub_doc\": 68.9, \"clinic_doc\": 0.0, \"grant_fund\": -911088.4, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('bdcd9dd6e5584f9b5f8eeb551a267cb0','f90e9c061ea63f3d762a3d1141314989','30640b686e5be896faa3d14ed6691346','2023-09-05 18:55:23','2023-10-29 05:31:13','Life Science','Next Generation Biology','Synthetic Biology','Biosensor',48,'A biosensor is an analytical device, used for the detection of a chemical substance, that combines a biological component with a physicochemical detector. The sensitive biological element, e.g. tissue, microorganisms, organelles, cell receptors, enzymes, antibodies, nucleic acids, etc., is a biologically derived material or biomimetic component that interacts with, binds with, or recognizes the analyte under study. The biologically sensitive elements can also be created by biological engineering. The transducer or the detector element, which transforms one signal into another one, works in a physicochemical way: optical, piezoelectric, electrochemical, electrochemiluminescence etc., resulting from the interaction of the analyte with the biological element, to easily measure and quantify. The biosensor reader device connects with the associated electronics or signal processors that are primarily responsible for the display of the results in a user-friendly way.','{\"pat_doc\": 9808.0, \"pub_alt\": 3920.0, \"pub_doc\": 33303.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 2318.0, \"clinic_alt\": 108.0, \"clinic_doc\": 162.0, \"grant_fund\": 989358162.0, \"pat_granted\": 3181.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 137.4, \"pub_doc\": 867.1, \"clinic_doc\": 19.0, \"grant_fund\": -13437491.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('be0c5bf791cea4f198bb51e0e78344ed','9be33f727d7b72fef24f5c1785693e63','968e5d71e0d0c5dc526e2a9156a8d9aa','2023-09-08 10:00:06','2023-10-28 19:31:14','Life Science','Sustainability/Core','Separations','supercritical fluid chromatography',24,'Supercritical fluid chromatography is a form of normal phase chromatography that uses a supercritical fluid such as carbon dioxide as the mobile phase. It is used for the analysis and purification of low to moderate molecular weight, thermally labile molecules and can also be used for the separation of chiral compounds. Principles are similar to those of high performance liquid chromatography, however SFC typically utilizes carbon dioxide as the mobile phase; therefore the entire chromatographic flow path must be pressurized. Because the supercritical phase represents a state in which liquid and gas properties converge, supercritical fluid chromatography is sometimes called convergence chromatography.','{\"pat_doc\": 102.0, \"pub_alt\": 270.0, \"pub_doc\": 303.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 9.0, \"clinic_alt\": 0.0, \"clinic_doc\": 1.0, \"grant_fund\": 786179.0, \"pat_granted\": 51.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": -1.0, \"pub_doc\": -10.3, \"clinic_doc\": 0.1, \"grant_fund\": -373175.7, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('c0131251b8f3723ddd5c211a36f61c77','46bdeb9160300133a73dc543b9ff12d8','e2208eebd283dcf9b3906ac407a5d224','2023-09-08 02:23:43','2023-10-28 14:31:13','Healthcare','Cardio-metabolic diseases','Thyroids & Endocrinology','Gigantism',36,'Gigantism, also known as giantism, is a condition characterized by excessive growth and height significantly above average. In humans, this condition is caused by over-production of growth hormone in childhood, resulting in people up to 2.7 m in height. It is a rare disorder resulting from increased levels of growth hormone before the fusion of the growth plate which usually occurs at some point soon after puberty. This increase is most often due to abnormal tumor growths on the pituitary gland. Gigantism should not be confused with acromegaly, the adult form of the disorder, characterized by somatic enlargement specifically in the extremities and face.','{\"pat_doc\": 3.0, \"pub_alt\": 7410.0, \"pub_doc\": 336.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 13.0, \"clinic_alt\": 1.0, \"clinic_doc\": 4.0, \"grant_fund\": 5502544.0, \"pat_granted\": 2.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": -0.9, \"pub_doc\": -6.1, \"clinic_doc\": 0.7, \"grant_fund\": -404062.4, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('c013e2d79437ab78b1091b9e9befe3fb','3ade3404fcd2fca0da04003e7692173a','556dd84c0895390f86a0e55de1ce00fb','2023-09-08 09:14:40','2023-10-28 21:16:12','Life Science','Sustainability/Core','Separations','Fourier-transform infrared',48,'Fourier transform spectroscopy is a measurement technique whereby spectra are collected based on measurements of the coherence of a radiative source, using time-domain or space-domain measurements of the electromagnetic radiation or other type of radiation.','{\"pat_doc\": 55.0, \"pub_alt\": 2087.0, \"pub_doc\": 15080.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 77.0, \"clinic_alt\": 47.0, \"clinic_doc\": 2.0, \"grant_fund\": 19967220.0, \"pat_granted\": 12.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 1.9, \"pub_doc\": 132.8, \"clinic_doc\": 0.6, \"grant_fund\": 254292.6, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('c028d965fb14837cac272f0fca5ff48e','3826e17fd1b8b38d7108087bc8b07908','22c986a1ed138cca635623e24850cd2d','2023-09-08 02:47:26','2023-10-28 14:01:15','Healthcare','Fertility','Novel therapies','Progesterone supplementation',48,'Progesterone supplementation, also known as progesterone therapy, is a medical treatment that involves taking supplemental doses of progesterone hormone. Progesterone is naturally produced by the ovaries during a womans menstrual cycle and plays a crucial role in regulating the menstrual cycle and preparing the body for pregnancy. However, some women may have low levels of progesterone, resulting in irregular menstrual cycles or difficulty getting pregnant. Progesterone supplementation can help balance hormonal levels and increase the chances of conceiving and sustaining a pregnancy. It can be administered through various methods, such as pills, injections, or vaginal suppositories, and is usually prescribed by a healthcare professional based on the patients individual needs and medical history.','{\"pat_doc\": 0.0, \"pub_alt\": 269.0, \"pub_doc\": 172.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 5.0, \"clinic_alt\": 0.0, \"clinic_doc\": 42.0, \"grant_fund\": 733852.0, \"pat_granted\": 0.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 0.0, \"pub_doc\": 2.6, \"clinic_doc\": 3.4, \"grant_fund\": -80930.6, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('c066d05766cb81150fc4c9b555eff1bc','82841277cc54621d2d6071e3ec919414','0b9a93bcbf56042557d5a41dd3db0243','2023-09-20 17:31:16','2023-10-28 13:01:19','Healthcare','Discovery & Development Technologies','Other','Waldo',36,'Telemanipulator, or waldo, is a device which, through electronic, hydraulic, or mechanical linkages, allows a hand-like mechanism to be controlled by a human operator.','{\"pat_doc\": 8.0, \"pub_alt\": 1938.0, \"pub_doc\": 1119.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 88.0, \"clinic_alt\": 0.0, \"clinic_doc\": 10.0, \"grant_fund\": 1838311.0, \"pat_granted\": 2.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 0.6, \"pub_doc\": 12.9, \"clinic_doc\": 2.4, \"grant_fund\": -590542.6, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('c0ac7730ff87d48e3e70871f397776cf','86bfc1d6ea6ada0972bb4ebd56d88ad7','8f2884ac2f89f569ae690ad0aa820ccc','2023-09-08 01:08:24','2023-10-28 15:41:15','Healthcare','Future therapeutic modalities','Cell therapies','Tumor-associated antigens',48,'Tumor-associated antigens (TAAs) are proteins that are present in cancer cells but not in normal cells or are expressed at higher levels in tumors than in healthy tissues. These antigens may be recognized by the immune system as foreign and trigger an immune response against the cancer cells. TAAs are being studied for their potential use in cancer vaccines and immunotherapy. However, many TAAs are also present in normal tissues, which can lead to side effects when targeted by cancer treatments. Therefore, the specificity of TAAs and their potential impact on healthy tissues must be carefully evaluated before their use in clinical settings.','{\"pat_doc\": 356.0, \"pub_alt\": 289.0, \"pub_doc\": 1038.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 55.0, \"clinic_alt\": 504.0, \"clinic_doc\": 34.0, \"grant_fund\": 45883064.0, \"pat_granted\": 55.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": -4.6, \"pub_doc\": 27.2, \"clinic_doc\": 6.4, \"grant_fund\": -3038596.8, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('c0bc0cc81732ecdad0525a98552833bf','eb2ca5cdbf466432efa3cad3dd594f1a','6725d42f932d0e446e761f0968e0172f','2023-09-08 02:04:06','2023-10-28 23:16:12','Life Science','Novel Modalities','Cell Therapy','Cell Characterization',48,'Cell Characterization is the process of understanding the physical, chemical, and biological properties of a specific type of cell. It involves analyzing various aspects of the cell, such as morphology, size, and structure, as well as its function and behavior. Through this process, scientists can gain a deeper understanding of how cells function, how they interact with other cells, and how they respond to different environments or stimuli. Cell Characterization is an essential tool for researchers and scientists in a variety of fields, including cell biology, genetics, and immunology, as it allows for the development of new treatments and therapies for diseases and the discovery of new biological mechanisms.','{\"pat_doc\": 61.0, \"pub_alt\": 496.0, \"pub_doc\": 502.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 69.0, \"clinic_alt\": 2.0, \"clinic_doc\": 5.0, \"grant_fund\": 47627377.0, \"pat_granted\": 10.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": -0.5, \"pub_doc\": 13.4, \"clinic_doc\": 0.3, \"grant_fund\": -513209.5, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('c0bd46c25aac04ff0f6290b7c109542a','bcec320c1d366012496fdc05b1162aad','3e072ff4f027f97184b7ecfb791122b7','2023-09-05 22:06:34','2023-10-28 17:26:11','Healthcare','Future therapeutic modalities','Delivery methods','Bacteriophages',24,'A bacteriophage, also known informally as a phage, is a duplodnaviria virus that infects and replicates within bacteria and archaea. The term was derived from \"bacteria\" and the Greek Ï†Î±Î³Îµá¿–Î½, meaning \"to devour\". Bacteriophages are composed of proteins that encapsulate a DNA or RNA genome, and may have structures that are either simple or elaborate. Their genomes may encode as few as four genes and as many as hundreds of genes. Phages replicate within the bacterium following the injection of their genome into its cytoplasm. Bacteriophages are among the most common and diverse entities in the biosphere. Bacteriophages are ubiquitous viruses, found wherever bacteria exist. It is estimated there are more than 10Â³Â¹ bacteriophages on the planet, more than every other organism on Earth, including bacteria, combined.','{\"pat_doc\": 340.0, \"pub_alt\": 653.0, \"pub_doc\": 2651.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 187.0, \"clinic_alt\": 247.0, \"clinic_doc\": 24.0, \"grant_fund\": 61220062.0, \"pat_granted\": 65.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": -4.4, \"pub_doc\": 69.6, \"clinic_doc\": 4.7, \"grant_fund\": -11975247.8, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('c145e3a638ec0d305f5764ae645d5e9e','7286b6dd5e6f51fb279c0a6a82e528d2','4cfacc6752b10fbede9acf0bca84032d','2023-09-08 02:52:18','2023-10-28 21:21:14','Life Science','Next Generation Biology','Tissue and Cell Culture','Cell Line Culture',48,'Cell line culture refers to the process of growing and propagating cells in vitro, outside the organism from which they were derived. The cells are typically obtained from tissues or organs and are cultured in a laboratory using specialized techniques and growth media. Cell line cultures are used extensively in research, drug development, and biomedical applications to study cell behavior, cell function, and disease processes, among other things. They are an important tool for understanding the mechanisms of diseases and for developing new drugs and therapies. In addition, they offer a reliable and reproducible model system that is easily manipulated, making them an attractive option for a wide range of applications. Overall, cell line culture has revolutionized scientific research and is a critical tool in advancing medical knowledge and treatments.','{\"pat_doc\": 23.0, \"pub_alt\": 15.0, \"pub_doc\": 148.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 17.0, \"clinic_alt\": 4.0, \"clinic_doc\": 1.0, \"grant_fund\": 1689690.0, \"pat_granted\": 12.0, \"companies_num\": 0.0, \"investors_num\": 0.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}','{\"pat_doc\": 0.1, \"pub_doc\": 4.0, \"clinic_doc\": -0.1, \"grant_fund\": -149953.0, \"capital_raised\": 0.0}'),('c19206e28add7c5149feab34ccb71649','9be33f727d7b72fef24f5c1785693e63','968e5d71e0d0c5dc526e2a9156a8d9aa','2023-09-08 10:00:06','2023-10-28 19:31:14','Life Science','Sustainability/Core','Separations','supercritical fluid chromatography',48,'Supercritical fluid chromatography is a form of normal phase chromatography that uses a supercritical fluid such as carbon dioxide as the mobile phase. It is used for the analysis and purification of low to moderate molecular weight, thermally labile molecules and can also be used for the separation of chiral compounds. Principles are similar to those of high performance liquid chromatography, however SFC typically utilizes carbon dioxide as the mobile phase; therefore the entire chromatographic flow path must be pressurized. Because the supercritical phase represents a state in which liquid and gas properties converge, supercritical fluid chromatography is sometimes called convergence chromatography.','{\"pat_doc\": 206.0, \"pub_alt\": 270.0, \"pub_doc\": 623.0, \"deals_num\": 0.0, \"grant_doc\": 29.0, \"clinic_alt\": 0.0, \"clinic_d